// Key Concepts:
// JWT - JSON Web Token, used for stateless authentication
// Bearer Token - Token passed in Authorization header
// Claims - Key-value pairs inside JWT (UserId, Role etc.)
// Authorize attribute - Protects controller/action from unauthorized access
// AllowAnonymous - Skips authentication for specific controller/action
// CORS - Cross Origin Resource Sharing, allows API access from other domains
// JwtSecurityToken - .NET class to create/read JWT tokens
// SymmetricSecurityKey - Same key used to sign and verify JWT
// HmacSha256 - Hashing algorithm used to sign the JWT